OL,3,C'Would be better' if Tory MPs selected
OL,4,Cleader, says Lord Hague
OL,6,FKemi Badenoch, Robert Jenrick, James
OL,7,FCleverly and Tom Tugendhat are all
OL,8,Fvying for the party leadership, and
OL,9,Fwill get a chance to address the
OL,10,Fparty's membership at the conference
OL,11,Fin Birmingham which gets under way on
OL,12,FSunday.
OL,14,FSpeaking to the BBC's Westminster
OL,15,FHour, Lord Hague ` who led the party
OL,16,Fafter its defeat in 1997 ` said that
OL,17,Fmembership had "become so small".
