OL,3,C'Would be better' if Tory MPs selected
OL,4,Cleader, says Lord Hague
OL,6,FLord Hague warned the winner that
OL,7,Fthere will be "a long haul".
OL,9,FAsked in the same Westminster Hour
OL,10,Finterview what advice he would give
OL,11,Fthe winner, he said: "The Labour
OL,12,Fgovernment will be vulnerable, even in
OL,13,Ffour or five years' time.
OL,15,F"But that does not mean that people
OL,16,Fwill see the Conservatives as the
OL,17,Fnatural replacement for them, unless
OL,18,Fwe have a very single-minded leader
OL,19,Fwho can communicate values, appeal to
OL,20,Fnew generations and talk about the
OL,21,Fissues of the future."
